<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENAP70B9B06014" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "01" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Side Sill Outer Panel Removal and Installation
</title>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
The figure below shows condition where following parts are removed.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Front fender 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B9A06005"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A9B0091.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "55.869mm" ver = "02" gw = "227" gh = "142"/>
</figure>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B9B06014001">
<title>
General Notes
</title>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Welding method and number of welding points are the same on both sides. This repair instruction shows procedure for left side.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Part filled with foamed material is included in parts of this repair. Therefore, repair referring to 
<intxref refid = "AENAP70B9B06022">Foamed Material Filling Area Repair</intxref>
 for precautions and repair procedure.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
The dimensions shown in the figure are reference values when cutting replacement part placed on top of existing part. Determine most appropriate cutting (or joint) line considering both size of replacement part and condition of existing part.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B9B06014002">
<title>
Removal
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Mark at the shown position and cut side sill outer panel.
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
Do not damage parts underneath side sill outer panel when cutting.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Drill out welding spots.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Bend open 3 metal tabs (arrow) and remove side sill outer panel.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70A9B0012.jpg" width = "183.000mm" height = "224.691mm" ver = "01" gw = "498" gh = "620"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "2" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.472in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "6.442in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
<symbol name = "MANOTE" width = "5.132mm" height = "3.048mm"/>
1:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
When heating around foamed material application portion to detach foamed material, be sure that temperature of said portion does not reach 170 &#176;C (338 &#176;F).
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
<symbol name = "MANOTE" width = "5.132mm" height = "3.048mm"/>
2:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
When heating around sealer application portion to detach body sealer, be sure that temperature of said portion does not reach 170 &#176;C (338 &#176;F).
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B9B06014003">
<title>
Installation
</title>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Before conducting any weld, check installation position and condition for installation part(s). 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B9B04006"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
 / 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B9B04007"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Proceed repair while taking into consideration installation of parts that affect appearance. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B9B04003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install new side sill outer panel to vehicle body and cut in stacked condition.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Repair foamed material. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B9B06022"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Apply sealer to side sill outer panel.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install side sill outer panel.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Conduct resistance spot weld and plug weld.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Conduct continuous weld.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Apply anticorrosion wax to back side of continuous weld part.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Bend in 3 metal tabs (arrow) of side sill outer panel.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70A9B0013.jpg" width = "183.000mm" height = "241.297mm" ver = "01" gw = "507" gh = "667"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "6" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.316in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "1.974in"/>
<colspec colnum = "3" colname = "3" colwidth = "0.316in"/>
<colspec colnum = "4" colname = "4" colwidth = "1.817in"/>
<colspec colnum = "5" colname = "5" colwidth = "0.316in"/>
<colspec colnum = "6" colname = "6" colwidth = "2.466in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
1.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Foamed material
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
3.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Rear door hinge reinforcement
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "5" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
5.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "6" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Applied part of body sealer.
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
2.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Side sill outer panel
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
4.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Side sill strength
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "5" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
<symbol name = "MANOTE" width = "5.132mm" height = "3.048mm"/>
:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "6" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Conduct resistance spot weld as three panel thickness.
</ptxt>
</entry>
